.TH "si_copy_dma" 9 "si_copy_dma" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
si_copy_dma \- copy pages using the DMA engine
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct radeon_fence *" si_copy_dma
.BI "(struct radeon_device *rdev "  ","
.BI "uint64_t src_offset "  ","
.BI "uint64_t dst_offset "  ","
.BI "unsigned num_gpu_pages "  ","
.BI "struct dma_resv *resv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rdev" 12
radeon_device pointer
.IP "src_offset" 12
src GPU address
.IP "dst_offset" 12
dst GPU address
.IP "num_gpu_pages" 12
number of GPU pages to xfer
.IP "resv" 12
reservation object to sync to
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Copy GPU paging using the DMA engine (SI).
Used by the radeon ttm implementation to move pages if
registered as the asic copy callback.
